    <!-- Help content -->
    <string name="help_overview_text">OpenCode Remote lets you monitor and interact with OpenCode sessions running on your server from your Android device.\n\n• Browse all sessions across directories\n• Create and delete sessions\n• Send prompts and slash commands\n• View messages, todos, and file diffs\n• Select AI agents and models\n\nConfigure your server connection in Settings to get started.</string>
    <string name="help_server_text">OpenCode Server Requirements:\n\n• OpenCode running with --server or serve mode\n• HTTP API accessible from your device\n• Basic Auth credentials configured\n\nDefault port: 4096\nIf using HTTPS, include the scheme in the host field.</string>
    <string name="help_network_text">Connection Tips:\n\n• For local servers, use your machine\'s LAN IP\n• For remote servers, use a domain name or public IP\n• HTTPS is recommended for remote connections\n• If behind a reverse proxy, use port 443\n• Cleartext HTTP is allowed for local development</string>
    <string name="help_troubleshooting_text">Common Issues:\n\n• Connection failed: Check host, port, and credentials\n• No sessions: Ensure OpenCode is running with projects\n• Messages not loading: Check server logs for errors\n• Timeout: Increase server timeout or check network\n• SSL errors: Ensure certificate is valid or use HTTP locally</string>

